<br>
Human Bard of Prexus<br>
Neutral Alignment<br>
<br>
The only thing I did not see in quick reading is the use of stun when I was a cleric.  I almost always had the two divines and the lower level root and stun in four of my spots.  Not everyone may agree, but root and stun were quick casting and helped me a bunch in dungeons.  Sometimes I even had the two lowest level stuns up.  Anyway I hope this helps. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ualainifv.showPublicProfile?language=EN>AlainiFV</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 8<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(6/17/02 1:01 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm45.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=27.topic&index=22>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Clerics of Norrath, lend me your ears! :-)</span><hr size=1> 1. What race are you? - Halfling - Short and Cute!<br>
<br>
2. What level are you? - 32!<br>
<br>
3. What deity do you follow? - Bristlebane<br>
<br>
4. What alignment are you on FV? - Discord Neutral<br>
<br>
5. What is one piece of advice for a new Cleric?<br>
<br>
Try to find a few people you enjoy spending time together with in your young years.....it really makes a difference when you know you can trust your groumembers.  I group with several friends nightly that I have known since season 14 or lower....their the best.  I know I will rarely die as they always keep me alive &lt;i can rez, don't ya know *chuckles&gt; or at the worst...they will be by my side till my spirit is brought back to my body. *Smile*<br>
